                        <tr>
                                <td colspan="2"><span class="postbody"></span><table width="90%" cellspacing="1" cellpadding="3" border="0" align="center"><tr> 	  <td><span class="genmed"><b>Quote:</b></span></td>	</tr>	<tr>	  <td class="quote">
<br />
Greetings Norrathians,
<br />

<br />
I would like to add this quick clarification to the update message, clarifying the charm effect change.
<br />
If the NPC was in the middle of casting a spell when charm is broken, it will interrupt the spell. After all, the creature is no longer interested in following the orders of a former master. 
<br />

<br />
Brenlo the Charming
<br />
</td>	</tr></table><span class="postbody">
<br />

<br />
Personally, I like it when an NPC stops to cast some crappy spell on me after a charm breaks, but this nerf was justified in order rectify the Tactics situation.  However, it is wrong that we get an npc_01 that will interrupt its currently casting spell when charm is broken, yet if we charm that same npc_01 who is casting CH on npc_02 the CH will still go through uninterrupted.  It's clear using Brenlo's reasoning that NPC spells ought to be interrupted under both situations.</span><span class="postbody"></span><span class="gensmall"></span></td>
                        </tr>
                </table></td>
