                        <tr>
                                <td colspan="2"><span class="postbody">Doing that was just silly, it didn't fix the exploit at all.
<br />

<br />
Here's how it happens now:
<br />

<br />
Exploiter charms a zek initiate.
<br />

<br />
Sends initiate after a war wraith.
<br />

<br />
War wraith begins to cast a spell.
<br />

<br />
Exploiter clicks insta invis item.
<br />

<br />
Initiate turns from Wraith and chases caster.
<br />

<br />
Wraith's spell lands on Initiate.
<br />

<br />
Initiate turns and chases Wraith (which has begun to chase the caster now)
<br />

<br />
Initiate hits wraith, wraith returns aggro. 
<br />

<br />
Exploiter pulls dozens of mobs to the area with the initiate and the wraith fighting and everyone joins into the huge fight.
<br />

<br />
Exploiter continues to pull mobs to the fight, getting exp for every mob that dies.
<br />

<br />
Before this 'fix' you could charm a caster (Who has more MR anyway so why would you bother?) or a melee.  Now you can only charm a melee, which was the easier of the 2 anyway.  Ooooh good fix Sony!
<br />

<br />

<br />
I tried this and it works.  It was fun but not fun enough to risk getting banned over.  
<br />

<br />
That being said, I wish they'd make this where no one got loot or exp.  It's just fun to do it and if it gave nothing back, it would still be fun to show your friends.  <img src="images/smiles/icon_biggrin.gif" alt="icon_biggrin.gif" border="0" /></span><span class="postbody"></span><span class="gensmall"></span></td>
