Actually Brenlo's reasoning makes this work as well, since after charm breaks he would clearly still want to heal his friend, since it's NOT the instruction of it's former master (you didn't tell it to complete heal his friend). That's why it works like it does.
<br />

<br />
I expect this is a temporary "quick fix" till they can get the factions fixed properly to prevent this exploit from happening again. I'd wager that fixing the faction system takes more work from teams working on the expansion so they changed the way charm works to decrease the ease of the exploit, while giving a large public warning that it's a bannable offence. Sort of a first step to quiet the population until they can get around to giving it the treatment it deserves.  <img src="images/smiles/icon_smile.gif" alt="icon_smile.gif" border="0" /></span><span class="postbody"><br />_________________<br />When I was young I used to pray to God that He would give me a new bicycle. I soon found out that God didn't work that way, so I stole a bike and asked Him to forgive me.
